Fellow gospel singer Rebecca Malope has also expressed her condolences to the Ncwane family. JOHANNESBURG - President Jacob Zuma has sent condolences to the family and friends of gospel singer Sfiso Ncwane.The multi-award winning star died this morning at the Fourways Life Hospital after suffering kidney failure.Zuma says Ncwane's death is a massive loss for the country as he had touched the hearts of millions of people.Ncwane was well known for being the first gospel singer to win Song of the Year at the South African Music Awards. Fellow gospel singer Rebecca Malope says Ncwane was also like a son to her. She has sent out her condolences to the singer's family. He was one of my children in the gospel industry and we happened to share a song together on stage when I was doing my live DVD in Soweto. Malope says Ncwane will be missed by all in the music industry.WATCH: Sfiso Ncwane- Kulungile(Edited by Neo Koza)